# Graph model

## Node data (`ConceptNodeData`)

```ts
interface ConceptNodeData {
  text: string; // concept label
  conf: number; // confidence 1–5
  reviewed: number; // days since last review
  pinned: boolean; // pinned nodes are not deleted by review pruning
}
```

## Edge categories and relation types

All edges carry a `data.type: EdgeTypeName`. The full definition lives in `src/data/edgeTypes.ts`.

| Category     | `EdgeTypeName` values                                   |
| ------------ | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| `taxonomic`  | `is-a`, `instance-of`, `subtype-of`                     |
| `structural` | `part-of`, `made-of`, `contains`                        |
| `causal`     | `causes`, `produces`, `enables`, `prevents`, `triggers` |
| `dependency` | `requires`, `uses`                                      |
| `temporal`   | `precedes`, `occurs-in`                                 |
| `opposition` | `contrasts-with`, `opposite-of`                         |

Each `EdgeTypeDef` has:

- `cat: EdgeCategory` — which category it belongs to
- `line: 'solid' | 'dashed' | 'dotted' | 'double' | 'wavy'` — stroke style
- `glyph: GlyphKind` — SVG icon at the target end
- `symmetric: boolean` — true for `contrasts-with` and `opposite-of`
- `label: string` — human-readable label

## Visual encoding

`NessoEdge` renders each edge according to its `EdgeTypeDef`. The amount of visual information shown depends on the `edgeEncoding` setting:

- `full` — line style + glyph + optional label
- `category` — colour only (category colour, no glyph)
- `minimal` — plain line, no glyph or colour distinction

Category colours are CSS custom properties (`--cat-taxonomic`, `--cat-structural`, etc.) set by the active palette in `src/data/palettes.ts`.

## React Flow edge type

All edges in the store use `type: 'nesso'`, mapped to `NessoEdge` in `GraphCanvas`. Never use the default React Flow edge types — they do not carry glyph or line-style rendering.
